wl-draft-config-alist support 'forward' key

Like as 'reply' key, when you invoke wl-summary-forward, you can
perform matching in original message buffer.

Fix quoted name encode/decode issue in draft mode.

If there is quoted name which contains white space and non-ascii
character in address list field, such as To: Cc:, it is
mis-decoded while saving and re-editing.  This commit partially
fix the issue.  When field value is not valid, the problem would
still occurs.

* wl/wl-draft.el (wl-draft-save): Use
eword-encode-unstructured-field-body for address list only when
field value is invalid.

Cf. https://github.com/wanderlust/wanderlust/pull/226

* elmo/elmo-imap4.el (elmo-imap4-read-response): Handle the case
that connection is broken.

Merge branch 'lastquarter' of https://github.com/catap/wanderlust into catap-lastquarter

(wl-biff-check-folder-async): Return non-nil when really start
async check or return nil.  Don't do synchronous check.

commit.message:
Fix for RAR archive format

The `rar v` output format has been changed long ago that no longer
matches the regexp. Change to use `rar lb` which produces content list
in format identical to tar.

* elmo/elmo-archive.el (elmo-archive-file-regexp-alist)
(elmo-archive-rar-method-alist): Reflect to the recent version of rar
command.

The `rar v` output format has been changed long ago that no longer
matches the regexp. Change to use `rar lb` which produces content list
in format identical to tar.

* elmo/elmo-archive.el (elmo-archive-file-regexp-alist)
(elmo-archive-rar-method-alist): Reflect to the recent version of rar
command.

Support conditional highlighting of message text

When wl-highlight-body-too is a list of major mode name's symbols,
highlight is enabled in specified major mode or MIME entity
situation's major mode.

Setting wl-highlight-body-too to nil means that highlight is also
disabled on message mode.  If you want previous behavior, change value
like below.

(setq wl-highlight-body-too '(wl-original-message-mode))

Similar change is applied on wl-highlight-text/diff.
